title: Nazareth girls soccer team beats Central Catholic
text:
Complete Box Score » 
Nazareth 2, Central Catholic 0 — Rapid Recap 
Nazareth senior forward Amy Strauser scored two goals a minute apart in the first half to lift the Blue Eagles to a 2-0 road win over Central Catholic on Thursday. 
Turning point : After a few early Vikings chances, Strauser found the back of the net following a pass from freshman midfielder Madison Amy with 32:04 left in the first half to get the momentum for the Blue Eagles. 
Top performer: Strauser, a captain, followed her first goal with a successful strike with 31:03 remaining in the first half. Her two early goals set the tone for the Blue Eagles the rest of the afternoon. 
What it means : Nazareth gets its 10th win of the season and bounces back from a tie against Emmaus and a loss to Whitehall in its last two games.
